dcterms:description: Aqueous solubility is the chemical saturated concentration in the aqueous phase, which is usually described with unit log(mol/L) and written as logS. This dataset includes 1,311 assay records and is used for binary classification to distinguish soluble or insoluble compounds.
dcterms:title: Aqueous Solubility

dcterms:creator: Richard B van Breemen
Yongmei Li
dcterms:description: Caco-2 cell permeability assay measures the rate of flux of a chemical across polarized Caco-2 cell monolayers, predicting drug in vivo absorption. The dataset consists of 7,624 assayed data points.
dcterms:title: Caco-2 Cell Permeability

dcterms:creator: Kristien Mortelmans
Errol Zeiger
dcterms:description: Ames mutagenesis assay uses bacteria to test whether a given chemical can cause mutations in the DNA of the test organism. The dataset includes 7,617 assayed data points, with a cut-off for binary classification based on the number of colonies.
dcterms:title: Ames Mutagenesis
